.SH NAME
bb-pr-merge - Merge a pull request


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbb pr merge  [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Merge an open pull request in Bitbucket Cloud. bb uses the destination branch default merge strategy when Bitbucket exposes one, or falls back to the repository default when Bitbucket does not include strategy metadata on the pull request. Accepts a numeric ID, pull request URL, or pull request comment URL.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--close-source-branch\fP[=false]
	Close the source branch when the pull request is merged

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for merge

.PP
\fB--host\fP=""
	Bitbucket host to use

.PP
\fB--jq\fP=""
	Filter JSON output using a jq expression

.PP
\fB--json\fP[=""]
	Output JSON with the specified comma-separated fields, or '*' for all fields

.PP
\fB--message\fP=""
	Merge commit message

.PP
\fB--repo\fP=""
	Bitbucket repository target as , /, or a repository URL

.PP
\fB--strategy\fP=""
	Merge strategy to use; required when Bitbucket does not expose a default

.PP
\fB--workspace\fP=""
	Optional workspace slug used only to disambiguate a bare repository target


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--no-prompt\fP[=false]
	Do not prompt for missing input, even in an interactive terminal


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  bb pr merge 7
  bb pr merge 7 --repo workspace-slug/repo-slug
  bb pr merge 7 --strategy merge_commit
  bb pr merge 7 --message 'Ship feature' --close-source-branch --json
  bb pr merge https://bitbucket.org/workspace-slug/repo-slug/pull-requests/7#comment-15
.EE


